# The ingest image builds from the REPO ROOT, because it needs two lanes' files: C's
# backend/ingest/app and A's db/exports.py. A root context is dangerous by default — this repo holds
# multi-GB Valhalla tiles and OSM extracts (backend/mapmatch/data), plus .git and venvs, none of
# which must ever be shipped to the daemon.
#
# So: exclude everything, then re-include exactly what the image needs. Deny-by-default means a new
# large directory can't silently bloat the build.
*

!backend/ingest/requirements.txt
!backend/ingest/app/
!db/exports.py

# ...and never let build artefacts ride along inside the re-included paths (these rules come last,
# so they win over the re-includes above).
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
